President Obama and Prime Minister Kan of Japan met to discuss various issues including economic, security, and regional cooperation. They reaffirmed their commitment to strengthening the U.S.-Japan alliance and discussed recent developments in Northeast Asia. They also pledged joint efforts in responding to threats from North Korea and Iran, as well as assisting with reconstruction in Afghanistan and Pakistan. The President raised the challenge of promoting economic growth and they agreed to make progress on economic issues during upcoming APEC meetings. They also discussed maritime issues in the western Pacific and ways to intensify cooperation in clean energy and nuclear security.